  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <div class="max-w-[700px] mx-auto px-8 sm:px-6 mt-[20vh]">
    <h1 class="text-black font-medium text-[48px] leading-[1.2] tracking-[-0.02em] sm:text-display mb-20">Products People Actually Want</h1>
    
    <h2 class="body-xxl font-semibold mb-12">A Designer's Guide to Building Better</h2>
    
    <p class="body-xxl mb-12">We're drowning in products nobody wants, built by people who never asked if they should.</p>

    <p class="body-xxl mb-12">Every day, thousands of new apps, websites, and digital products launch. Most will be forgotten within six months—not because they don't work, but because nobody needed them in the first place.</p>

    <p class="body-xxl mb-12">After 25+ years designing digital products and leading teams at companies like IKEA, Herman Miller, and Summer Health, I've learned that the difference between products people love and products they abandon isn't about features, aesthetics, or even usability.</p>

    <p class="body-xxl mb-24"><strong>It's about understanding humans well enough to build things they actually want.</strong></p>

    <!-- Book Cover -->
    <OptimizedImage 
      src="/images/anton.webp" 
      alt="Products People Actually Want book cover" 
      className="w-full mb-24"
    />

    <!-- Book Description -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-12">This book cuts through the noise</h2>
    
    <p class="body-xxl mb-12">Most design books talk in circles about theory and best practices. This one addresses the work as it is: messy trade-offs, pressure to ship, the challenge of balancing business goals with real user needs.</p>
    
    <p class="body-xxl mb-8">You'll learn:</p>
    <ul class="body-xxl list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-4 mb-12">
      <li>Why "everyone is a designer" and how to leverage diverse perspectives in your team</li>
      <li>The complete product design process that works in the real world, not just in case studies</li>
      <li>How to communicate design decisions and influence stakeholders who "prefer the other option because it looks more modern"</li>
      <li>Practical frameworks for user research that reveal what people actually need (not what they say they want)</li>
      <li>How to design for anyone without falling into the "design for everyone" trap</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p class="body-xxl mb-24"><strong>This isn't another book about making things pretty. It's about making things work.</strong></p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-12">Start reading now</h2>
  </div>

